textDisplay: The unsung hero of the series. His character is a testament to giving good advice but never taking it yourself. He was born with a good heart and even when he was on bender that heart remained true. There are millions of people like this, crippled by alcohol or drugs that mask whatever pure and genuine good that is inside them.

textDisplay:
I know that everyone says how Fiona raised those kids, but she didn't do it alone like she says she did. Lip was there. Lip helped raise them as she raised Lip. Without Lip Fiona wouldn't have been able to do what she did, she needs Lip in order to raise the kids. I know he isn't always the best, but he is always there whenever his siblings need him. Lip raised those kids just as much as Fiona did.
They both raised their siblings, and they both did a good job. They balanced each other out, and without each other they wouldn't have been able to do it.
